tracing and tracing-subscriber are dependencies but not initialized.

**Issue:** Logging dependencies exist but no initialization code

**Why it matters:**
- --verbose and --log-level flags in spec require tracing setup
- No logging output will appear without initialization
- Debug/troubleshooting will be difficult
- Users expect verbose mode to work

**Fix:**
Create logging initialization in src/cli/mod.rs or src/main.rs:
```rust
use tracing_subscriber::{fmt, EnvFilter};

pub fn init_logging(verbose: bool, log_level: Option<&str>) {
    let filter = log_level
        .map(|l| EnvFilter::try_new(l).unwrap_or_default())
        .unwrap_or_else(|| {
            if verbose {
                EnvFilter::new("info")
            } else {
                EnvFilter::new("warn")
            }
        });

    tracing_subscriber::fmt()
        .with_env_filter(filter)
        .with_writer(std::io::stderr)  // Keep stdout for JSON output
        .init();
}
```

Call from main() after parsing CLI args.

