In src/cli/commands/tree.rs lines 264-267, the cycle detection code is dead code that never executes:

```rust
if path.contains(id) {
    return Ok(Some(node));
}
path.insert(id.clone());
```

The check on line 264 happens AFTER the expanded.insert() check at line 256. If we just inserted into expanded, the id can't be in path yet (we haven't inserted into path). 

Cycles are actually caught by line 283 `if path.contains(&child.id)` which skips children that are ancestors.

Impact: Low - cycles are still handled correctly, but there's dead/confusing code.

Fix: Remove the dead code at lines 264-267:
```rust
// Remove these lines:
if path.contains(id) {
    return Ok(Some(node));
}
```

Keep the path.insert(id.clone()) for actual cycle detection via the child check.

