In clippy.rs lines 104-113, when cargo clippy exits with non-zero status, errors are double-counted.

When clippy fails due to deny lints or compilation errors, those errors are already counted in the parsing loop (lines 82-87). Adding another errors += 1 here double-counts them.

Impact: Score calculation will be incorrect (penalized 10 extra points for the same error).

Fix: Only add the synthetic error if no actual errors were parsed, or track whether the failure was due to a clippy lint vs a compilation issue.

```rust
// Current (buggy):
if clippy_failed {
    errors += 1;  // This adds +1 to errors
    details.push(ClippyIssue { ... });
}

// Fix option 1: Only add if no errors parsed
if clippy_failed && errors == 0 {
    errors += 1;
    details.push(ClippyIssue { ... });
}
```

