When Version::parse fails, is_stable() returns true (stable), which is backwards.

**File:** src/core/analyzers/crates_io.rs lines 160-165

**Current code:**
```rust
fn is_stable(version: &str) -> bool {
    match Version::parse(version) {
        Ok(parsed) => parsed.pre.is_empty(),
        Err(_) => true,  // Bug: treating unparseable as stable
    }
}
```

**Why it matters:** If crates.io returns malformed version string, code incorrectly treats it as stable. Could recommend upgrading to broken/invalid version.

**Fix:**
```rust
fn is_stable(version: &str) -> bool {
    match Version::parse(version) {
        Ok(parsed) => parsed.pre.is_empty(),
        Err(_) => false,  // Conservative: don't recommend unparseable versions
    }
}
```

**Acceptance:** Unparseable versions are treated as unstable

